	(text_box "NUMITRON DISPLAY:\n- powering from 2.8V to 4.5V with power consumption up to 22,5mA per segment.\n- smooth transition between segment changes using PWM to account for 10x lower resistance when the filaments are cold.\n- according to the original datasheet the frequency of the PWM should NOT be between 105Hz and 1kHz in order to avoid mechanical resonance.\n- the lifespan of a classic light bulb is assumed to be proportional to the 13th to 14th power of the supply voltage."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 260.35 322.58 0)
		(size 121.3484 20.3199)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
